The Senator representing Nasarawa West Senatorial District, Abdullahi Adamu, has formally written the Upper Chamber disclosing his resignation from the Ninth Senate. Senator Adamu, former Governor of Nasarawa State said his resignation followed his emergence as the National Chairman of the  All Progressives Congress (APC). Similarly, Senator Abubakar Kyari (Borno North) also resigned from the Senate following his emergence as APC Deputy National Chairman (North) The President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan read their letters at plenary on Tuesday.